WYNDHAM CHAMPIONSHIP
August 18, 2013
Ryo Ishikawa
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   What do you do next?  
RYO ISHIKAWA:   I'm going to my home, a week off and then play the Web.com final events.   I'll play and then get my card for next year.  
   
 Q.   Was it a hard decision or did you --  
RYO ISHIKAWA:   No.   I have confidence for my game now so I'm pretty excited.   I'm actually looking forward to next four events and hopefully getting out there and see you guys on next year, too, this field.  
   
 Q.   You like the prospects of playing four events like that to build your way into it?   
RYO ISHIKAWA:   Yeah, I do.   Actually I love it, I love this place for playing golf.   I love it.   What can I say?   Yeah.  
   
 Q.   You feel good about your game where it is right now?  
RYO ISHIKAWA:   Yeah.   My short game is much better than six months, three months ago.   This couple weeks of I've played well so, yeah.   I made cut last week, too so, my game is getting better.   My tee shots was almost perfect just for my iron and -- I adjusted for two weeks.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT